'''{{PAGENAME}}''' is an ancient Egyptian festival ==Overview==
==References== [[Category:Egyptian festival pages to be written]] [[Category:qq]][[sn:Neith Festival (Esna)]][[Category:qq]] [[Category:pages to be translated]] [[en:Neith Festival (Esna)]] [[Category:pages created from Interlanguage links]] [[de:Neith-Fest (Esna)|12=draft]]
[[Category:ancient Egyptian festivals]] [[Category:qq]][[sn:Neith Festival (Esna)]][[Category:qq]] {{Egyptian Calendar Navbar}}

{{Infobox hieroglyphs
|TITLE = Khnum Temple in Esna
|NAME = <hiero>O6-X1:O1-W9-E10-A40</hiero><br />Hut-Chenmu<br />''Ḥwt-H̱nmw''<br />''House of {{ill|Chnum|de|Chnum|ja|クヌム|zh|克努姆|12=draft}}''
|IMAGE1 = Esna Temple 2004 by John Campana.jpg
|IMAGE1-WIDTH = 290px
|IMAGE1-DESCRIPTION = Khnum Temple of Esna
}}

The “'''Neith Festival'''”, which was solemnly celebrated in the {{ill|Temple of Esna|de|Tempel von Esna|ja|エスナの神殿|zh|埃斯纳神庙|12=draft}} as the “{{ill|Creation|de|Schöpfung|ja|創造|zh|创造|12=draft}} Festival” on {{ill|Ipip|de|Ipip|ja|イピップ|zh|伊皮普|lt=13. Epiphi|lt_ja=13. エピフィ|lt_de=13. Epiphi|lt_zh=13. 伊皮普|12=draft}}, the third month of the {{ill|Shemu#Dating|de|Schemu#Datierungen|ja|シェム#Datierungen|zh|Schemu#Datierungen|lt=Shemu Season|lt_ja=シェムの季節|lt_de=Schemu-Jahreszeit|lt_zh=Schemu季节}}, was celebrated in this special {{ill|Esna|de|Esna|ja|エスナ|zh|埃斯纳|12=draft}} form at no other place of {{ill|Ancient Egypt|de|Altägypten|ja|古代エジプト|zh|古埃及|12=draft}}.

The Neith Festival was regarded as the female {{ill|Counterpart|de|Pendant|ja|カウンターパート|zh|对应物|12=draft}} of the {{ill|Khnum Festival|de|Chnum-Fest|ja|クヌム祭|zh|克努姆节|12=draft}} “{{ill|Fixing of the Potter's Wheel|de|Festsetzen der Töpferscheibe|ja|陶芸車輪の固定|zh|固定陶轮|12=draft}}”, which was celebrated in Esna simultaneously with the {{ill|Dendera|de|Dendera|ja|デンデラ|zh|丹德拉|12=draft}} Festival “{{ill|Raising of the Sky (Ptah)|de|Erheben des Himmels (Ptah)|ja|Ptahのための天の掲揚|zh|为Ptah举天|lt=Raising of the Sky for Ptah|lt_ja=Ptahのための天の掲揚|lt_de=Erheben des Himmels für Ptah|lt_zh=为Ptah举天|12=draft}}”. Reasons for this are found in the special significance of {{ill|Chnum|de|Chnum|ja|クヌム|zh|克努姆|12=draft}} and {{ill|Neith (Egyptian Mythology)|de|Neith (ägyptische Mythologie)|ja|エジプト神話のネイス|zh|埃及神话中的Neith|12=draft}} in Esna, who were worshipped there as creator deities.

The festival {{ill|symbolized|de|symbolisierte|ja|象徴した|zh|象征了|12=draft}} the creation of Ancient Egypt, with the thematic complex including eight primordial gods, thirty additional gods, the births of {{ill|Re (Egyptian Mythology)|de|Re (ägyptische Mythologie)|ja|エジプト神話のラー|zh|埃及神话中的Re|12=draft}}, {{ill|Apophis|de|Apophis|ja|アポフィス|zh|阿波菲斯|12=draft}}, as well as {{ill|Thoth|de|Thot|ja|トート|zh|托特|12=draft}} and the creation words of the Neith-Methyer. The celebration began on the evening of the previous day with the procession to {{ill|Sais|de|Sais|ja|セイス|zh|塞斯|12=draft}}, where torches, candles, and other objects were lit:
{{Zitat|Lighting of torches inside the temple. The men and women celebrate a beautiful day, the whole city rejoices, so that there is no sleep for anyone until dawn.|Excerpt from {{ill|Esna 207|de|Esna 207|ja|エスナ207|zh|埃斯纳207|12=draft}}<ref name=L87>Alexandra von Lieven: ''The Sky over Esna.'' Wiesbaden 2000, p. 87.</ref>}}

{{ill|Herodotus|de|Herodot|ja|ヘロドトス|zh|希罗多德|12=draft}} reports,<ref>Herodotus, ''Histories'' Book 2, 62.</ref> that the custom of lighting torches followed by the ensuing celebration was also practiced outside of Sais. It is therefore likely that this festival practice provided the festive framework everywhere.<ref name=L87/>

== Literature ==
* Maria-Theresia Derchain-Urtel: ''The Visual and Textual Design in Esna.'' In: {{ill|Ursula Verhoeven-van Elsbergen|de|Ursula Verhoeven-van Elsbergen|ja|ウルズラ・フェアホーヴェン＝ファン・エルスベルゲン|zh|乌苏拉·费霍文-范-埃尔斯贝尔根|lt=Ursula Verhoeven|lt_ja=ウルズラ・フェアホーヴェン|lt_de=Ursula Verhoeven|lt_zh=乌苏拉·费霍文|12=draft}}, {{ill|Erhart Graefe|de|Erhart Graefe|ja|エルハルト・グレーフェ|zh|埃尔哈特·格雷费|12=draft}} (eds.): ''Religion and Philosophy in Ancient Egypt. Festschrift for Philippe Derchain on his 65th birthday on 24 July 1991'' (= ''Orientalia Lovaniensia Analecta. (OLA).'' Volume 39). Department of Oriental Studies, among others, Leuven 1991, ISBN 90-6831-337-1, pp. 107–121.
* {{ill|Alexandra von Lieven|de|Alexandra von Lieven|ja|アレクサンドラ・フォン・リーエン|zh|亚历山德拉·冯·利文|12=draft}}: ''The Sky over Esna. A Case Study on Religious Astronomy in Egypt on the Example of the Cosmological Ceiling and Architrave Inscriptions in the Temple of Esna'' (= ''Egyptological Treatises. (ÄA).'' Volume 64). Harrassowitz, Wiesbaden 2000, ISBN 3-447-04324-5 (Also: Tübingen, Univ., Master's thesis, 1998).

